+## Self-host with Docker
+
+CodeDeck Hosted is an additional web edition for a Linux server. It does **not** replace the Tauri desktop application: the normal Windows, macOS, and Linux desktop builds continue to work as before.
+
+### Requirements
+
+- A Linux server with Docker Engine
+- Docker Compose v2 (`docker compose`)
+- An existing directory containing the projects you want to manage
+
+### Install
+
+```bash
+git clone https://github.com/JadnK/CodeDeck.git
+cd CodeDeck
+chmod +x hosted/setup.sh
+./hosted/setup.sh /srv/projects
+```
+
+Replace `/srv/projects` with the absolute path to your projects directory. The setup script creates `hosted/.env`, generates a random access token, keeps the web service bound to `127.0.0.1:8080`, and starts the published `ghcr.io/jadnk/codedeck-web:latest` image. If the image is not available yet, it builds the hosted edition locally.
+
+Open CodeDeck securely from your computer with an SSH tunnel:
+
+```bash
+ssh -L 8080:127.0.0.1:8080 user@your-server
+```
+
+Then visit `http://127.0.0.1:8080`. Read the generated login token on the server with:
+
+```bash
+grep '^CODEDECK_WEB_TOKEN=' hosted/.env
+```
+
+### Update an installation
+
+```bash
+git pull --ff-only
+docker compose --env-file hosted/.env -f hosted/compose.yml pull
+docker compose --env-file hosted/.env -f hosted/compose.yml up -d --remove-orphans
+```
+
+Use `latest` for stable release images or change `CODEDECK_IMAGE` in `hosted/.env` to `ghcr.io/jadnk/codedeck-web:edge` to follow every push to `main`.
+
+By default, CodeDeck Hosted is reachable only from the server itself. Keep that default and use an SSH tunnel, VPN, or HTTPS reverse proxy; do not expose port 8080 directly to the public internet. Commands run inside the container and can modify files in the mounted projects directory.
+
+See [`hosted/README.md`](hosted/README.md) for operations, security details, toolchains, and development instructions.
+
 ## Getting started
 
 1. Install and open CodeDeck.
