+# Hosted Web Edition
+
+CodeDeck Hosted is an optional Docker-based web edition for projects stored on a Linux server. It runs alongside the normal Tauri desktop application and does not replace or modify the desktop build.
+
+## Before you start
+
+You need:
+
+- a Linux server
+- Docker Engine
+- Docker Compose v2
+- an absolute directory containing the projects CodeDeck may access
+
+The hosted backend can read and write files under the mounted projects directory and can run commands inside the container. Only mount trusted projects and only run trusted commands.
+
+## Install
+
+```bash
+git clone https://github.com/JadnK/CodeDeck.git
+cd CodeDeck
+chmod +x hosted/setup.sh
+./hosted/setup.sh /srv/projects
+```
+
+Replace `/srv/projects` with your actual projects directory.
+
+The setup script:
+
+1. verifies Docker and Docker Compose
+2. generates a random 256-bit bearer token
+3. stores configuration in `hosted/.env` with restrictive file permissions
+4. binds CodeDeck to `127.0.0.1:8080`
+5. pulls the stable GHCR image or builds it locally when necessary
+6. starts the container with Docker Compose
+
+## Connect securely
+
+The default localhost binding is intentional. Create an SSH tunnel from your computer:
+
+```bash
+ssh -L 8080:127.0.0.1:8080 user@your-server
+```
+
+Open `http://127.0.0.1:8080` in your browser. Retrieve the token on the server with:
+
+```bash
+grep '^CODEDECK_WEB_TOKEN=' hosted/.env
+```
+
+For permanent remote access, use a VPN or an HTTPS reverse proxy with authentication. Do not publish port 8080 directly to the internet.
+
+## Common commands
+
+Check status:
+
+```bash
+docker compose --env-file hosted/.env -f hosted/compose.yml ps
+```
+
+Follow logs:
+
+```bash
+docker compose --env-file hosted/.env -f hosted/compose.yml logs -f codedeck
+```
+
+Restart:
+
+```bash
+docker compose --env-file hosted/.env -f hosted/compose.yml restart codedeck
+```
+
+Stop:
+
+```bash
+docker compose --env-file hosted/.env -f hosted/compose.yml down
+```
+
+The named data volume is preserved when the container is stopped or recreated.
+
+## Update
+
+```bash
+git pull --ff-only
+docker compose --env-file hosted/.env -f hosted/compose.yml pull
+docker compose --env-file hosted/.env -f hosted/compose.yml up -d --remove-orphans
+```
+
+The default image is `ghcr.io/jadnk/codedeck-web:latest`, which follows stable releases. To test every successful push to `main`, set this in `hosted/.env`:
+
+```env
+CODEDECK_IMAGE=ghcr.io/jadnk/codedeck-web:edge
+```
+
+## Desktop and hosted behavior
+
+The editions share compatible configuration concepts, but their native backends are separate:
+
+- Desktop backend: Rust and Tauri in `src-tauri/`
+- Hosted backend: Node.js in `hosted/server/`
+
+Frontend or data-model changes may need to be reflected in both editions. A Rust-only change does not automatically change the hosted server.
+
+## Available toolchains
+
+The default image includes Node.js, npm, pnpm, Yarn, Git, SSH, Python 3, and common native build tools. Rust, Java, Go, Docker CLI, and project-specific services are not included by default. Extend `hosted/Dockerfile` when your server projects need additional toolchains.
+
+## Security defaults
+
+- bearer-token authentication is required
+- the service binds to localhost by default
+- filesystem access is restricted to the mounted projects root
+- symlink escapes and traversal attempts are rejected
+- the container runs as an unprivileged user
+- Linux capabilities are dropped
+- the root filesystem is read-only
+- the Docker socket is not mounted
+
+These controls reduce risk, but CodeDeck still executes user-selected commands against mounted project files. Treat access to the hosted UI like shell-level developer access to those projects.
